get suspended.

266
00:18:41,667 --> 00:18:43,633
How's your godsister?

267
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:46,500
She's okay, Sir.

268
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:52,700
Sorry, Sir, for being stubborn
about our mission.

269
00:18:55,133 --> 00:19:00,167
Enriquez, you've been stubborn
not just on this mission,

270
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:02,767
even in Manila,
you were stubborn.

271
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:05,200
I'm this close to beat you.

272
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:08,267
Okay, Sir, beat me.

273
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,367
But I can't blame you...

274
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,933
because I know
what you're going through.

275
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:19,333
I did the same thing...

276
00:19:19,467 --> 00:19:21,000
for Lara.

277
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,100
But I'm happy that...

278
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:29,400
you saved your godsister.

279
00:19:32,867 --> 00:19:34,900
It was a team effort, Sir.

280
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:39,600
If not for you
and Lieutenant Garcia,

281
00:19:39,733 --> 00:19:41,967
I wouldn't have saved
my godsister.

282
00:19:43,033 --> 00:19:44,000
So...

283
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:44,933
thank you, Sir.

284
00:19:45,067 --> 00:19:47,533
I should thank you too.

285
00:19:47,667 --> 00:19:48,900
What for?

286
00:19:49,033 --> 00:19:50,800
When Lara was gone...

287
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:55,567
my only motivation
to become a police officer

288
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:58,167
was to avenge her death

289
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:00,667
by going after those
who killed her.

290
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:05,433
My anger consumed me.

291
00:20:08,033 --> 00:20:09,633
But because of you,

292
00:20:09,767 --> 00:20:12,467
I remembered why
I became a police officer.

293
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:15,133
It's because I want to fight
for what's right...

294
00:20:16,567 --> 00:20:19,267
and protect all the people
who are important to me.

295
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,833
So when we return
to the Philippines,

296
00:20:23,967 --> 00:20:26,333
I'm ready to be a good police
officer again.

297
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:30,133
Like the police officer that...

298
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:34,433
Lara loved back then.

299
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:37,533
For sure, Lara must be proud
and happy for you, Sir.

300
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:48,300
Bok...

301
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:49,733
I'm amazed...

302
00:20:50,433 --> 00:20:52,333
we were great earlier.

303
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:56,533
Imagine, we beat
the whole syndicate.

304
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:58,933
Don't worry.

305
00:20:59,067 --> 00:21:02,767
I'll tell the chief
not to suspend us anymore.

306
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:04,167
This stays between us, okay?

307
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:05,500
He's scared of me.

308
00:21:06,867 --> 00:21:07,933
Thank you, Sir.

309
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,167
You're so great.

310
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:10,600
I know, I know.

311
00:21:10,733 --> 00:21:12,067
But you...

312
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:14,033
you were great earlier as well.

313
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:15,267
Which one, Sir?

314
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:18,000
When we were about to go in.
The part where you said...

315
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:20,667
Excuse me...

316
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:23,000
It's so hot here.

317
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:23,633
I like...

318
00:21:23,767 --> 00:21:25,133
Do you have water?

319
00:21:25,267 --> 00:21:26,867
Do you have wine?

320
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:30,633
That was awesome.

321
00:21:30,767 --> 00:21:34,533
It's a good thing the guards
are weak, unlike me.

322
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:38,433
Because if you did that to me,
it wouldn't be effective.

323
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:40,400
Here, listen to this...

324
00:21:40,533 --> 00:21:42,933
When I was still
in kindergarten,

325
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:44,267
going to grade school,

326
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:46,133
they were already
doing that to me.

327
00:21:46,267 --> 00:21:49,267
Actually, one of my classmates
came up to me.

328
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,667
She said, "Excuse me,

329
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,633
do you have water?
Do you have..."

330
00:21:52,767 --> 00:21:53,767
I didn't give her water!

331
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:55,300
I didn't get carried away!

332
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:58,267
Well, to this day,
they're still teasing her.

333
00:22:03,633 --> 00:22:05,067
You idiots.

334
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:08,567
How did three Calabari
police officers

335
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:11,133
ruin our operation
in Switzerland?

336
00:22:11,267 --> 00:22:15,600
And worse,
they got Selena alive.

337
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:18,633
You really are idiots,
aren't you?

338
00:22:22,067 --> 00:22:26,067
You'd better get
your people ready.

339
00:22:26,633 --> 00:22:28,333
Because after the elections...

340
00:22:29,133 --> 00:22:32,833
I want you to finish off
Enriquez and Conde.

341
00:22:39,767 --> 00:22:41,167
Glen!

342
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:43,700
Who are you talking to?

343
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:46,067
Did I hear that right?

344
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,967
You're going to finish off
Sergeant Enriquez

345
00:22:49,133 --> 00:22:51,700
and Lieutenant Conde?

346
00:23:08,433 --> 00:23:10,967
With all the evidence and
witnesses we have against you,

347
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:14,700
life in prison awaits.

348
00:23:14,833 --> 00:23:19,433
But if you cooperate with us,
your sentence can be reduced.

349
00:23:19,567 --> 00:23:22,667
Sergeant Enriquez and Lieutenant
Conde are my idols.

350
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:23,833
There you go!

351
00:23:23,967 --> 00:23:26,000
A mix of acid and NBOMe.

352
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:29,667
It's like a level up of LSD,
so it's really potent.

353
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:32,267
So, does that mean just one
pimple patch can kill you?

354
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:33,233
What are you selling?

355
00:23:33,367 --> 00:23:34,367
Beauty products.

356
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:35,933
Are you selling pimple patches?

357
00:23:36,067 --> 00:23:37,167
- Hey!
- Oh, hey!

358
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:38,967
Hey! Stop!

359
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:42,667
Our goal is to identify the
seller of the pimple patches

360
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:43,267
at school.

361
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:44,900
So let's blend in first.

362
00:23:45,033 --> 00:23:46,700
It's better for both of us
to keep a low profile.

363
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:48,033
What's your plan, Conde?

364
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:49,667
You might not like it.

365
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:52,067
Wake up, we're going somewhere.

366
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,033
Pray, Markus,

367
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:55,433
because it's the end for you.
